If your OpenType font supports combining diacritics, be sure to include U+25CC DOTTED CIRCLE in your font, and optionally include this in your positioning rules for all your combining marks. This is because Uniscribe will insert U+25CC between "illegal" diacritic sequences (such as two U+064E characters in a row) to make the mistake more visible. (https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/typography/script-development/arabic#handling-invalid-combining-marks)
